An elderly woman and a young girl have been injured following a car crash on Dr Chota Motala Road, outside Northdale hospital on Thursday. Mi7 National group’s emergency medical services responded to the scene, along with SAPS. According to Brandon Drinkwater of Mi7 emergency services, the patients suffered minor injuries. “We attended to the patients and transported them to Eden Garden hospital,” said Drinkwater. He added that witnesses said the collision occurred due to the malfunctioning traffic lights near the Northdale hospital. “All we know for now is that the SAPS is still investigating the matter,” added Drinkwater.